Code for a simple HTML image gallery. This can be used to generate boilerplate
pages for any directory of images.

CSS, HTML, and Javascript for the image slider was originally sourced from
code examples at https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_image_gallery.asp

Note images should be named with leading zeros as shown below. Using my
https://github.com/chris-hunter206/image_optimize script will automatically
create the different sized image names that this script expects.

Directory structure should look like the following:

.
├── components
│   └── slider.js
├── css
│   └── gallery.css
└── images
    ├── image01.jpg
    ├── image01_med.jpg
    ├── image01_thumb.jpg
    ├── image02.jpg
    ├── image02_med.jpg
    ├── image02_thumb.jpg
    ├── image03.jpg
    ├── image03_med.jpg
    └── image03_thumb.jpg

1. Copy the gen_gallery_page.sh script to somewhere in your path, like $HOME/bin/
2. In the current directory, run the script like so:

 gen_gallery_page.sh > pagename.html
